transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra at Score Blue.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Yes, I received some kind of refill that I didn't order, so I want to know what's going on.

Speaker 2: Okay, sir. So let me pull up your prescription and see how it's written.

Speaker 1: Could you please provide me with the phone number associated with the account?

Speaker 2: 2-8-1-7-8-2-1-7-6-2.

Speaker 1: All right, so that's 2-8-1...

Speaker 2: 7-8-2-1-7-6-2.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And your full name and date of birth, please?

Speaker 1: Eduardo Leon.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: March 17, 1962.

Speaker 2: Thank you, thank you.

Speaker 1: So it looks like the doctor wrote the prescription for the 25-milligram Viagra back in August.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's required 25.

Speaker 1: And it looks like that was written with refills.

Speaker 2: So what happened was you had a refill go through in December.

Speaker 1: Now, it's perfectly adjustable, sir, so you're not required or obligated to do it this way.

Speaker 2: So if you wanted, you could just pause it, and that would allow you to call in and place orders as needed.

Speaker 1: Yes, can you do that, please?

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 1: Okay, I went ahead and paused it for you.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: Uh-huh, thank you.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
